      "writtenOn": "2017-09-01T18:12:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. No need to hardcode Method. LUCI context method will be picked up on its own if the binary runs in a context. I can also imagine a situation when we want to use \"user method\" (manual login), e.g when we standardize depot_tools to use luci token cache for everything (this will allow us to drop redundant .gitcookies).\n2. Please expose all auth options as flags by using https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/client/authcli/authcli.go#124. See https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/master/client/authcli/authcli.go#320 as full end-to-end example of almost exactly of what we want to do in the credentials helper.\n\nI assume there\u0027ll be a way to configure command line flags of the credential helper?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 54,
        "endLine": 49,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "97bae9e22cf88bba2329d8f6e64c992166179a56",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
